Template: lsmtpd/description
Type: note
Description: LSMTP â€” lightweight SMTP daemon
 Thank you for using LSMTP.
 .
 A compact, secure SMTP server that accepts incoming mail and forwards
 messages to an AMQP broker (for example RabbitMQ).
 .
 See the documentation and source code at https://lsmtp.nekonik.org and
 https://github.com/Neko-Nik/LSMTP.
 .
 For support or to report issues, contact admin@nekonik.com

Template: lsmtpd/rust_log
Type: select
Choices: TRACE, DEBUG, INFO, WARN, ERROR
Default: INFO
Description: LSMTP logging level
 Choose the logging level the daemon should use.

Template: lsmtpd/bind_address
Type: string
Default: 0.0.0.0
Description: Bind address
 The IP address the daemon should bind to.

Template: lsmtpd/bind_port
Type: string
Default: 25
Description: Bind port
 The port number the daemon should listen on.

Template: lsmtpd/server_name
Type: string
Default: nekonik.com
Description: Server name
 The hostname the server should present.

Template: lsmtpd/amqp_host
Type: string
Description: AMQP host
 The AMQP broker host (leave empty to disable if not configured).

Template: lsmtpd/amqp_port
Type: string
Description: AMQP port
 The AMQP broker port (leave empty to disable if not configured).

Template: lsmtpd/amqp_username
Type: string
Description: AMQP username
 The username used to connect to the AMQP broker.

Template: lsmtpd/amqp_password
Type: password
Description: AMQP password
 The password for the AMQP user (will not be shown on-screen when entered).

Template: lsmtpd/amqp_vhost
Type: string
Description: AMQP vhost
 The AMQP virtual host to use.

Template: lsmtpd/amqp_exchange
Type: string
Description: AMQP exchange
 The AMQP exchange to publish to.

Template: lsmtpd/amqp_routing_key
Type: string
Description: AMQP routing key
 The routing key to use when publishing messages.

Template: lsmtpd/amqp_buffer_size
Type: string
Default: 10
Description: AMQP buffer size
 The internal buffer size before flushing to AMQP.

Template: lsmtpd/max_email_size
Type: string
Default: 52428800
Description: Max email size (bytes)
 The maximum accepted email size in bytes.
